name: victini
flavor_text_en: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

name: snivy
flavor_text_en: It is very intelligent and calm. Being exposed to lots of sunlight makes its movements swifter.

name: servine
flavor_text_en: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.

name: serperior
flavor_text_en: It can stop its opponents’ movements with just a glare. It takes in solar energy and boosts it internally.

name: tepig
flavor_text_en: It can deftly dodge its foe’s attacks while shooting fireballs from its nose. It roasts berries before it eats them.

name: pignite
flavor_text_en: When its internal fire flares up, its movements grow sharper and faster. When in trouble, it emits smoke.

name: emboar
flavor_text_en: It can throw a fire punch by setting its fists on fire with its fiery chin. It cares deeply about its friends.

name: oshawott
flavor_text_en: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

name: dewott
flavor_text_en: Strict training is how it learns its flowing double-scalchop technique.

name: samurott
flavor_text_en: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.

name: patrat
flavor_text_en: Using food stored in cheek pouches, they can keep watch for days. They use their tails to communicate with others.

name: watchog
flavor_text_en: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

name: lillipup
flavor_text_en: It faces strong opponents with great courage. But, when at a disadvantage in a fight, this intelligent Pokémon flees.

name: herdier
flavor_text_en: It has black, cape-like fur that is very hard and decreases the amount of damage it receives.

name: stoutland
flavor_text_en: It rescues people stranded by blizzards in the mountains. Its shaggy fur shields it from the cold.

name: purrloin
flavor_text_en: They steal from people for fun, but their victims can’t help but forgive them. Their deceptively cute act is perfect.

name: liepard
flavor_text_en: These Pokémon vanish and appear unexpectedly. Many Trainers are drawn to their beautiful form and fur.

name: pansage
flavor_text_en: This Pokémon dwells deep in the forest. Eating a leaf from its head whisks weariness away as if by magic.

name: simisage
flavor_text_en: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

name: pansear
flavor_text_en: When it is angered, the temperature of its head tuft reaches 600° F. It uses its tuft to roast berries.

name: simisear
flavor_text_en: It loves sweets because they become energy for the fire burning inside its body.

name: panpour
flavor_text_en: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

name: simipour
flavor_text_en: The tuft on its head holds water. When the level runs low, it replenishes the tuft by siphoning up water with its tail.

name: munna
flavor_text_en: Munna always float in the air. People whose dreams are eaten by them forget what the dreams had been about.

name: musharna
flavor_text_en: The mist emanating from their foreheads is packed with the dreams of people and Pokémon.

name: pidove
flavor_text_en: Each follows its Trainer’s orders as best it can, but they sometimes fail to understand complicated commands.

name: tranquill
flavor_text_en: It can return to its Trainer’s location regardless of the distance separating them.

name: unfezant
flavor_text_en: Males swing their head plumage to threaten opponents. The females’ flying abilities surpass those of the males.

name: blitzle
flavor_text_en: When thunderclouds cover the sky, it will appear. It can catch lightning with its mane and store the electricity.

name: zebstrika
flavor_text_en: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

name: roggenrola
flavor_text_en: Its ear is hexagonal in shape. Compressed underground, its body is as hard as steel.

name: boldore
flavor_text_en: When it overflows with power, the orange crystal on its body glows. It looks for underground water in caves.

name: gigalith
flavor_text_en: Compressing the energy from its internal core lets it fire off an attack capable of blowing away a mountain.

name: woobat
flavor_text_en: Its habitat is dark forests and caves. It emits ultrasonic waves from its nose to learn about its surroundings.

name: swoobat
flavor_text_en: It emits sound waves of various frequencies from its nose, including some powerful enough to destroy rocks.

name: drilbur
flavor_text_en: It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

name: excadrill
flavor_text_en: It can help in tunnel construction. Its drill has evolved into steel strong enough to bore through iron plates.

name: audino
flavor_text_en: It touches others with the feelers on its ears, using the sound of their heartbeats to tell how they are feeling.

name: timburr
flavor_text_en: It fights by swinging a piece of lumber around. It is close to evolving when it can handle the lumber without difficulty.

name: gurdurr
flavor_text_en: This Pokémon is so muscular and strongly built that even a group of wrestlers could not make it budge an inch.

name: conkeldurr
flavor_text_en: It is thought that Conkeldurr taught humans how to make concrete more than 2,000 years ago.

name: tympole
flavor_text_en: They warn others of danger by vibrating their cheeks to create a high-pitched sound.

name: palpitoad
flavor_text_en: When they vibrate the bumps on their heads, they can make waves in water or earthquake-like vibrations on land.

name: seismitoad
flavor_text_en: They shoot paralyzing liquid from their head bumps. They use vibration to hurt their opponents.

name: throh
flavor_text_en: When it tightens its belt, it becomes stronger. Wild Throh use vines to weave their own belts.

name: sawk
flavor_text_en: The sound of Sawk punching boulders and trees can be heard all the way from the mountains where they train.

name: sewaddle
flavor_text_en: Leavanny dress it in clothes they made for it when it hatched. It hides its head in its hood while it is sleeping.

name: swadloon
flavor_text_en: Forests where Swadloon live have superb foliage because the nutrients they make from fallen leaves nourish the plant life.

name: leavanny
flavor_text_en: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves, using the cutters on its arms and sticky silk.

name: venipede
flavor_text_en: Its bite injects a potent poison, enough to paralyze large bird Pokémon that try to prey on it.

name: whirlipede
flavor_text_en: Protected by a hard shell, it spins its body like a wheel and crashes furiously into its enemies.

name: scolipede
flavor_text_en: With quick movements, it chases down its foes, attacking relentlessly with its horns until it prevails.

name: cottonee
flavor_text_en: When attacked, it escapes by shooting cotton from its body. The cotton serves as a decoy to distract the attacker.

name: whimsicott
flavor_text_en: Like the wind, it can slip through any gap, no matter how small. It leaves balls of white fluff behind.

name: petilil
flavor_text_en: The leaves on its head are very bitter. Eating one of these leaves is known to refresh a tired body.

name: lilligant
flavor_text_en: Even veteran Trainers face a challenge in getting its beautiful flower to bloom. This Pokémon is popular with celebrities.

name: basculin
flavor_text_en: Red and blue Basculin get along so poorly, they’ll start fighting instantly. These Pokémon are very hostile.

name: sandile
flavor_text_en: They live buried in the sands of the desert. The sun-warmed sands prevent their body temperature from dropping.

name: krokorok
flavor_text_en: They live in groups of a few individuals. Protective membranes shield their eyes from sandstorms.

name: krookodile
flavor_text_en: They never allow prey to escape. Their jaws are so powerful, they can crush the body of an automobile.

name: darumaka
flavor_text_en: When its internal fire is burning, it cannot calm down and it runs around. When the fire diminishes, it falls asleep.

name: darmanitan
flavor_text_en: Its internal fire burns at 2,500° F, making enough power that it can destroy a dump truck with one punch.

name: maractus
flavor_text_en: It uses an up-tempo song and dance to drive away the bird Pokémon that prey on its flower seeds.

name: dwebble
flavor_text_en: This Pokémon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

name: crustle
flavor_text_en: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

name: scraggy
flavor_text_en: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.

name: scrafty
flavor_text_en: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.

name: sigilyph
flavor_text_en: They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.

name: yamask
flavor_text_en: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

name: cofagrigus
flavor_text_en: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.

name: tirtouga
flavor_text_en: Restored from a fossil, this Pokémon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

name: carracosta
flavor_text_en: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.

name: archen
flavor_text_en: Said to be an ancestor of bird Pokémon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

name: archeops
flavor_text_en: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.

name: trubbish
flavor_text_en: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

name: garbodor
flavor_text_en: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

name: zorua
flavor_text_en: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

name: zoroark
flavor_text_en: Bonds between these Pokémon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

name: minccino
flavor_text_en: They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.

name: cinccino
flavor_text_en: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

name: gothita
flavor_text_en: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

name: gothorita
flavor_text_en: They use hypnosis to control people and Pokémon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.

name: gothitelle
flavor_text_en: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

name: solosis
flavor_text_en: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

name: duosion
flavor_text_en: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

name: reuniclus
flavor_text_en: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

name: ducklett
flavor_text_en: These bird Pokémon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food--peat moss.

name: swanna
flavor_text_en: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

name: vanillite
flavor_text_en: The temperature of their breath is -58° F. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.

name: vanillish
flavor_text_en: Snowy mountains are this Pokémon’s habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

name: vanilluxe
flavor_text_en: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and attack their foes with violent blizzards.

name: deerling
flavor_text_en: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

name: sawsbuck
flavor_text_en: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuck’s horns.

name: emolga
flavor_text_en: The energy made in its cheeks’ electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

name: karrablast
flavor_text_en: These mysterious Pokémon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.

name: escavalier
flavor_text_en: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.

name: foongus
flavor_text_en: It lures people in with its Poké Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a Poké Ball is unknown.

name: amoonguss
flavor_text_en: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble Poké Balls, in a swaying motion.

name: frillish
flavor_text_en: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

name: jellicent
flavor_text_en: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicent’s habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.

name: alomomola
flavor_text_en: The special membrane enveloping Alomomola has the ability to heal wounds.

name: joltik
flavor_text_en: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.

name: galvantula
flavor_text_en: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

name: ferroseed
flavor_text_en: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

name: ferrothorn
flavor_text_en: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.

name: klink
flavor_text_en: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

name: klang
flavor_text_en: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.

name: klinklang
flavor_text_en: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.

name: tynamo
flavor_text_en: While one alone doesn’t have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

name: eelektrik
flavor_text_en: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

name: eelektross
flavor_text_en: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

name: elgyem
flavor_text_en: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponent’s brain, causing unendurable headaches.

name: beheeyem
flavor_text_en: It can manipulate an opponent’s memory. Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three different-colored fingers.

name: litwick
flavor_text_en: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and Pokémon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

name: lampent
flavor_text_en: This ominous Pokémon is feared. Through cities it wanders, searching for the spirits of the fallen.

name: chandelure
flavor_text_en: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

name: axew
flavor_text_en: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.

name: fraxure
flavor_text_en: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after they’ve been fighting.

name: haxorus
flavor_text_en: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.

name: cubchoo
flavor_text_en: When it is not feeling well, its mucus gets watery and the power of its Ice-type moves decreases.

name: beartic
flavor_text_en: It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.

name: cryogonal
flavor_text_en: When its body temperature goes up, it turns into steam and vanishes. When its temperature lowers, it returns to ice.

name: shelmet
flavor_text_en: When attacked, it defends itself by closing the lid of its shell. It can spit a sticky, poisonous liquid.

name: accelgor
flavor_text_en: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

name: stunfisk
flavor_text_en: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.

name: mienfoo
flavor_text_en: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

name: mienshao
flavor_text_en: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.

name: druddigon
flavor_text_en: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.

name: golett
flavor_text_en: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.

name: golurk
flavor_text_en: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

name: pawniard
flavor_text_en: Blades comprise this Pokémon’s entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.

name: bisharp
flavor_text_en: It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.

name: bouffalant
flavor_text_en: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

name: rufflet
flavor_text_en: They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.

name: braviary
flavor_text_en: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.

name: vullaby
flavor_text_en: Their wings are too tiny to allow them to fly. They guard their posteriors with bones that were gathered by Mandibuzz.

name: mandibuzz
flavor_text_en: It makes a nest out of bones it finds. It grabs weakened prey in its talons and hauls it to its nest of bones.

name: heatmor
flavor_text_en: It breathes through a hole in its tail while it burns with an internal fire. Durant is its prey.

name: durant
flavor_text_en: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

name: deino
flavor_text_en: It tends to bite everything, and it is not a picky eater. Approaching it carelessly is dangerous.

name: zweilous
flavor_text_en: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

name: hydreigon
flavor_text_en: This brutal Pokémon travels the skies on its six wings. Anything that moves seems like a foe to it, triggering its attack.

name: larvesta
flavor_text_en: This Pokémon was believed to have been born from the sun. When it evolves, its entire body is engulfed in flames.

name: volcarona
flavor_text_en: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcarona’s fire provided a replacement for the sun.

name: cobalion
flavor_text_en: This legendary Pokémon battled against humans to protect Pokémon. Its personality is calm and composed.

name: terrakion
flavor_text_en: This Pokémon came to the defense of Pokémon that had lost their homes in a war among humans.

name: virizion
flavor_text_en: This Pokémon fought humans in order to protect its friends. Legends about it continue to be passed down.

name: tornadus
flavor_text_en: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

name: thundurus
flavor_text_en: Countless charred remains mar the landscape of places through which Thundurus has passed.

name: reshiram
flavor_text_en: This Pokémon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.

name: zekrom
flavor_text_en: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

name: landorus
flavor_text_en: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as “The Guardian of the Fields.”

name: kyurem
flavor_text_en: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

name: keldeo
flavor_text_en: By blasting water from its hooves, it can glide across water. It excels at using leg moves while battling.

name: meloetta
flavor_text_en: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

name: genesect
flavor_text_en: Over 300 million years ago, it was feared as the strongest of hunters. It has been modified by Team Plasma.
